    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static Bart getInstance()
                        throws IOException
        Retrieves a singleton instance of BART driver. The first call to this method copies the dll to the temp directory, and loads it, and returns with the driver call. The subsequent calls, however, only returns the already created driver class.
        Returns:
        singleton instance of BART driver
        Throws:
        IOException - when an error occurs during copying the dll to the temp directory

      • registerMemory

        public void registerMemory​(String name,
                           io.github.hakkelt.ndarrays.NDArray<?> array)
                    throws BartException
        Register an NDArray to allow BART to use them as input.
        • Example:
        
NDArray<Complex> array = new ComplexF32NDArray(128, 128).fill(new Complex(1,-1));
Bart bart = Bart.getInstance();
bart.registerMemory("input.mem", array);
bart.registerOutput("output.mem");
bart.execute("cabs", "input.mem", "output.mem");
NDArray<Complex> result = bart.loadResult("output.mem"));
bart.unregisterMemory("input.mem");
bart.unregisterMemory("output.mem");
assertEquals(array.abs(), result.squeeze().real());
        Parameters:
        name - the registered NDArray can be referenced by this name
        array - NDArray to be used as input for BART commands
        Throws:
        BartException - when JNI call fails for any reason

      • run

        public io.github.hakkelt.ndarrays.NDArray<org.apache.commons.math3.complex.Complex> run​(Object... args)
                                                                                 throws BartException
        Executes a BART command and reads its output to an NDArray

        Note: It is assumed that the BART command to be executed saves its output to a file and it expects the name of the file to be specified as the last argument. When passing arguments to this function, this last argument specifying the output file name should be omitted as it is handled automaticall by this driver.

        • Example:
        
NDArray<Complex> array = new ComplexF32NDArray(128, 128).fill(new Complex(1,-1));
Bart bart = Bart.getInstance();
NDArray<Complex> bartAbs = bart.run("cabs", array).squeeze();
        Parameters:
        args - name of BART command and its arguments
        Returns:
        NDArray that holds the output of the BART command
        Throws:
        BartException - when JNI call fails for any reason
